<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
OK Folks, here comes the time to really decide what we would like to have in our further planes.  I m thinking about that trouble since more than 3 weeks, and here are purposes I offer you to decide on, feel free to express all points you can have in your mind.<br>
<br>
- PoA isnt a real matter, so it will be added to the global decision.<br>
<br>
- PoF is the largest trouble we can meet, due to major Epic mobs dropped by Mini's, and due to its large respawn time.<br>
PoF really have to me retain into rotation.<br>
<br>
- PoH (new) could be considered as an open zone, but there is some major epic parts on this plane either. As the epic side has always been the &quot;tip&quot; to decide to put mobs into rotation, I guess we have to let new PoH in a rotation.<br>
But ... respawn time is faster than ever, and there is 2 twinked mobs which could be interesting for some <br>
<br>
That is why I suggest we :<br>
<br>
- Start again with ALL rotations like before<br>
- Nothing changes for PoA or PoF<br>
- Amend the PoH rule as follows : Only the UP guild has right to kill Mini's (excepted Maestro and Innoruk). Anyone else who want just discover the zone would be authorized to gather in. We will just ask them to be careful to not interfer with the regular up guild.<br>
Maestro and Innoruk would actually be FFA, as they are stronger than ever  We would look for a rotation on them the day they would be perma killed by number of different guilds.<br>
<br>
I hope I havent forgot something important, but feel free to correct or ask to amend all points, this is nothing else than a purpose.<br>
<br>
------------------<br>
Konhan Lovecraft<br>
Guild Leader of Armonia<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I think that this is a very sensible compromise and should appease the majority.<br>
<br>
Elvenador<br>
Office of TUS<br>
