<br>
What actually made a target a potential rotation target was if there was too much competition for it (i.e. Perma killed without guilds getting a chance at him ever unless you were waiting in it's room for it's spawn).  Simple as that.  Now, no targets have really been added to the rotations since Velious, and even then there were only a couple added.  Epic drops are coincidental, mostly because most of the biggest targets in Original and RoK dropped epic pieces, so that was to a certain extent incidental.  The epic drop status itself was not considered in whether a target went on rotation, just the competition level. <p>Farrnusno <BR>
